item.title: Tottenham And Bolton Players Reaction To What Happened To Fabrice Muamba
item.description:
Tottenham And Bolton Players Reaction To What Happened To Fabrice Muamba
Fabrice Ndala Muamba (born 6 April 1988) is a footballer who plays for Bolton Wanderers as a midfielder in the Premier League. He previously played for Arsenal and Birmingham City. At international level, he has represented England at under-21 level. On 17 March 2012 Muamba collapsed during an FA Cup tie between Bolton and Tottenham Hotspur on live international television and was rushed to hospital. The referee, Howard Webb, suspended, and later abandoned, the match just before halftime. Muamba's condition is currently not known, but is stated on the BBC to be "extremely serious". The ESPN live broadcast (carried on Fox Soccer Channel in the United States) also stated that the information on his condition had not been confirmed.
